63	\begin{remark}[Comparison with Mathlib's ring-level $\Omega_{B/A}$]
64	  \label{rem:kahler_compatibility}
65	  Mathlib provides the ring-theoretic K\"ahler differential module $\Omega_{B/A}$ together with the universal derivation $\mathrm{d} \colon B \to \Omega_{B/A}$. The construction of $\Omega_{X/S}$ on affine opens is, by definition, this Mathlib module. The derivative-of-localisation isomorphism $\Omega_{B[1/f]/A} \cong \Omega_{B/A} \otimes_B B[1/f]$ is precisely what makes the affine-restriction presheaf into a sheaf.
